The Ekiti State Police Command says that indigenes of the State, who participated in the physical screening of 2021 NPF recruitment exercise, will take part in the next phase, which is the Computer-Based Test (CBT). The command, in a press release dated 14th April, 2022, titled “Re: 2021 Recruitment of Constables into the Nigeria Police Force”, made available to DAILY POST through the Command’s PPRO, Sunday Abutu, noted that the exercise will hold on Wednesday 20th April, 2022, between the hours of 8:30 and 10:30 in the morning at the Afe Babalola University CBT Centre, Ado Ekiti. All applicants are to check their recruitment status on www.policerecuitment.gov.ng using their NIN and ensure they print out their examination slip. The Ekiti State Commissioner of Police, CP Moronkeji Adesina charged all eligible candidates to strictly adhere to the following instructions: “Be at the venue on time, appear in white shirts and white shorts, come along with the printout of their examination slips and NIN, as well as conduct themselves in an orderly manner.” He assured them of adequate security throughout the period of the exercise.